						<h4>Anjali Enjeti</h4>
												<p>Anjali Enjeti is a former attorney, journalist, activist, and election worker based near Atlanta. She is the author of two award-winning books, <em>Southbound: Essays on Identity, Inheritance, and Social Change</em>, and the novel, <em>The Parted Earth</em>. Her other writing has appeared in the <em>Los Angeles Times</em>, <em>Boston Globe</em>, <em>Harper’s Bazaar</em>, <em>Oxford American</em>, and elsewhere. She teaches creative writing in the MFA programs at Antioch University in Los Angeles and Reinhardt University in Waleska, Georgia.</p>
